11.always remember guys naloxone is shortlasting so its crucial you stay with the casualty letting them know the opiate is still in their system, they may well go back over always call 999 and if you dont carry naloxone please ask your local provider for a kit
10. here ricci and me move onto part2 of prenoxad kit assembly and demonstrate how to administer lifesaving naloxone for the purposes of saving a life
9. you can reverse an opiate overdose providing you carry lifesaving naloxone always! and know how to use it part one shows you how to assemble a prenoxad kit in preparation for administration

8. its so important that you know what your looking for so here ricci and me point out the signs & symptoms of an overdose always be on the look out guys and always give people a shout and a shake if your unsure overdose is reversible death is not

7. the effects opiates have on the body is really important to know as this can help you identify someone who is potentally overdosing always be on the look out guys, every life matters & we can stop the deaths
